	</tr>
	<tr>
		<td width="10%" nowrap="nowrap">Post subject:&nbsp;</td>
		<td><b>Nintendulator preference file location on Win7?</b></td>
	</tr>
	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />I've encountered an odd bug where Nintendulator's main window no longer appears on load. I can get it to show up if I maximize it by right-clicking on the taskbar, but it will not display in any other circumstance. I think it might be loading the window outside the size of my current display resolution. Is there a preference file I can delete to reset these positions?<br /><br />Thanks!

		

		</td>
	</tr>
	</table>


	<hr width="85%" />

	<table width="85%" cellspacing="3" cellpadding="0" border="0" align="center">
	<tr>
		<td width="10%" nowrap="nowrap">Author:&nbsp;</td>
		<td><b>thefox</b> [ Tue Nov 19, 2013 8:20 am ]</td>
	</tr>
	<tr>
		<td width="10%" nowrap="nowrap">Post subject:&nbsp;</td>
		<td><b>Re: Nintendulator preference file location on Win7?</b></td>
	</tr>
	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />Hold down shift, right click on Nintendulator's icon in the task bar and select Move (if move is disabled (= window is minimized), select Restore, then redo the step). Use arrow keys to move the window into view. After you press an arrow key for the first time, you can also use mouse to move the window.

		

		</td>
	</tr>
	</table>


	<hr width="85%" />

	<table width="85%" cellspacing="3" cellpadding="0" border="0" align="center">
